gomodel:SYNGO_4764  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: SGIP1α (854AA protein isoform from SGIP1 gene) interacts with Syt1 as shown by GST-pull down assays show reverse-IP\n\nFigure 2: SGIP1α co-localized with SYT1 in cultured hippocampal neurons and SGIP1α shRNA knockdown caused selective defects in the internalization of Syt1.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Primary rat hippocampal or cortical neurons derived from embryonic day 18 Sprague Dawley fetal rats of either sex were prepared as described previously\"\n\n\"We generated full-length SGIP1α (NM_001285852.1) by inserting additional amino acid sequence in GFP-SGIP1 template by PCR and then ligated into the XhoI-KpnI sites in HA-C1 vector and FLAG-C1 vector. By application of PCR site-directed mutagenesis, we prepared several SGIP1 mutation constructs: HA-SGIP1α-μHD (aa 550-854)\"\n\nmouse sequence that is over-expressed (hence we annotate against mouse protein, not the rat host system);\nQ8VD37-6 is the 854AA isoform, and uniprot gave this isoform the synonym SGIP1alpha.\n\nantibody:\nAnti-SGIP1 was purchased from Sigma-Aldrich (Merck, Darmstadt, Germany)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4764" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

